review_blob: I have had this bottle for a long time. I am pretty excited to try it! Pours a dark motor oil like color. Very thin head. Oh and gold cap on this bottle! Smells of oatmeal, some bourbon and some chocolate. Taste has a bunch of chocolate flavors with a smooth bourbon after taste. Slightly dry in the finish. Bit of an oatmeal cookie taste too! Delicious!
beer_name: Hoppin Frog Barrel Aged BORIS The Crusher

review_blob: Beer is lighter in color than I was expecting. Smells of some hops and brown sugar! Taste is sweet! Some hops and alcohol in the taste! Okay but not my favorite
beer_name: Evil Twin Molotov Cocktail Single Simcoe Hop Edition

review_blob: Pours an pale orange color with a nice head. Smells hoppy with some pine and grapefruit! Tastes a little sweet with brilliant hops all over! Mmm
beer_name: Flying Dog Imperial IPA - HBC-431 Single Hop

review_blob: This bottle is awesome! Looks like hot sauce! I had to buy it! Pours a blackish color with a foamy brown head. Smells a bit of coffee and a bit of spice! Dry mouth feel with lots of coffee and a nice spicy aftertaste that has a slight burning feeling. Mmmm

Pours an amber color with a nice sweet maple syrup aroma! I taste some apples and maple syrup in my mouth! Would pair very well with a bacon rich breakfast. Alas, I have no breakfast right now so the rating will reflect that.
Pours a nice rich black color with a foamy brown head. Smells sweet like candy. Taste is fairly rich with some coffee notes hidden in there. Decent beer.
beer_name: Left Hand Wake Up Dead Imperial Stout

review_blob: Beer pours a reddish brown color with a nice creamy looking off white head. Aroma is of sour cherries and some oak! Taste is of souring cherries and some bourbon aftertaste. Pretty creamy smooth finish. Nice balance of being not overly sour.
Pours a black color with a thin brown head. Smells slightly of coffee with some mild sweetness in the aroma. Pretty balanced taste. Not my favorite milk stout, however!
Pours a rich mahogany color. Rich sugary aroma with bourbon strong in the nose. Bit of brown sugar with some hops! Kinda weird taste I cant pinpoint in the aftertaste. Good tasting beverage
Pours a very black color with a creamy light brown head. Nice hop and coffee flavor. Pretty bitter and dry with some great coffee flavors! Pretty decent beer.
Pours a very light pale orange color with a bunch of yellow hues. Thin white head. Smells of lemon in the aroma. I taste lemon, grass, slight hops and some grapefruit.

Pours a rich brown color with a very thin off white head. Smells a bit of chocolate, dates and caramel. Pretty great smell. Taste is a bit sweet with some of that chocolate date like flavor coming through. Good stuff
I love Sierra Nevada beers. This one didnt disappoint. Nice bit of citrus with the hops. Some extra malts in the make it tasty.
Pours an orange color with a zangy spicy Chipotle smell. Has a dry mouth feel with some hops and smokey flavors. Pretty good.
Pours a orangey yellow color. Smells citrusy with a bit of an orange flavor. Taste has a bit of a tart after taste.
Pours a super light yellow color with a horribly skunky cardboard aroma. Taste is awful. Like corn and a 3 year old budweiser.

Oh no. I am enjoying this beer after 4/20. I have failed Stone Brewing Company. Pours an orange color with a great citrus atoms. Some great hop and pine flavors mixed with some grapefruit. I like this beer!

Oh well this beer is delicious! Brown color with some delicious bourbon flavors. Nice hop and malt balance. I taste the bourbon sweetness through this one with some brown sugar and a little hop bitterness in the finish!
Pours a reddish purple color with some brown in it. Smells like coconut and chocolate. Taste is like a delicious desert. Delicious.
Pours a brown color with a thin brown head. Smells of malts with a slight amount of RUM. Beer is very smooth! Sweet rum flavors with some nice hoppy flowery tastes.
beer_name: John Henry West Indies Pale Ale

review_blob: Pours a yellow color with a small head. Interesting smokey flavor that I am excited about. I dont taste a whole lot of the pineapple but there is a subtle hint of it in the beer. Smokey flavor is very prevalent. Good beer.
beer_name: Terrapin Side Project Pineapple Express Smoked Pineapple Helles

review_blob: Pours a hazy orange color. What a great smell this beer has! Delicious hops and grass and pine and hops! Love it. This is what an double IPA should smell like. Mmmm. Taste is pretty good too! Not as balanced as it could be. Still like this beer a lot. Pleasantly surprised by Pub dog. Perhaps I will go get one of their delicious pizzas to celebrate!

Pours a nice mahogany color with a very thin head. Pretty sweet aroma for a barelywine. I am not sensing many of the hops. Taste is sweet too! Malts, caramel and brown sugar all over the taste. Bit too sweet for me. And i dont taste a whole lot of hops!

Pours an ambery brown color with a hazy appearance. Has a bunch of floaties! Not sure if the beer is old or is supposed to have floaties! Smells of hops and molasses. Some nice brown sugar in the flavor with some bitter aftertastes. Good hoppy tastes.

Pours a dark black color with a foamy brown head. I can smell some coffee and chocolate. Taste is somehwat sweet. Chocolate like and all. Some coffee in the aftertaste. Nothing too special with this beer. Fairly good though.
Pours a murky brown color with a very thin head. Got this as a gift for helping someone. It is quite tasty. Lots of chocolate bar flavoring with some nuts in the flavor. Sweet and delicious.
Pours a hazy yellow orange color with a thin white head. Smells of wheat and citrus. Some spice in the aroma too. Taste is pretty good. Mmm

Pours a black color with a brown head. Head seems to stick around for awhile. I was expecting a commando unit to come into my house when I opened this bottle but no such thing happened. I am a bit disappointed. Smells like bourbon, wood and chocolate. I taste coffee, chocolate and some wood. Pretty dry finish with a coffee aftertaste. Tasty!
Pours a deep orange brown color with an off white head. Smells of malts and hops. Not much wood or bourbon in the aroma. Taste is that of wood and malts. Some hops too. Fairly decent flavors.
beer_name: Widmer Brothers Old Embalmer - Barrel Aged

review_blob: Pours a fairly pale orange yellow color with a strong piney aroma. Huge hop flavors which is expected in an Ipa. Little bit of a citrus under tone. Pretty tasty
beer_name: Flying Dog The Truth Imperial IPA

review_blob: Pours a black color similar to the devils heart. Smells a bit of coffee and caramel. Some sweet chocolate is also the aroma. Cant taste the ridiculous amount of alcohol in the beer. I say that wins as a beer.
beer_name: Struise Black Damnation IV - Coffee Club

review_blob: Nice dark color to this beer. Sweet caramel and chocolate flavors. Semi sweet but not overly sweet. I like this one
Pours a light golden color with a white head. Slightly hoppy with a dry mouth feel. Decent beer
Smells delicious. I get pumpkin, cinnamon, and some cherries? Cloves and pumpkin spice are all coming through. Some slight bourbon in the after taste.
beer_name: Uinta Crooked Line Oak Jacked Imperial Pumpkin

review_blob: I was excited for this beer mostly because i love Sierra Nevada beers. They are usually fairy hoppy. This one isnt so much. Kind of watery with a little of a dry after taste. Not my favorite but is organic. Im green now!!!
Pours a reddish brown color with an off white head. Smells slightly hoppy. Taste is dry and a bit bitter. More bitter than expected! Still a decent beer!

Pours a brownish orange color with a light brown head. Smells a bit like squash and maple syrup. Taste is a bit sweet with a little bit of a zingy aftertaste. Some pumpkin in the taste as well. Pretty delicious!
Taste is sweet. Sugary but with a weird smell. Aroma is kind of putting me off. Ooh well.
Pours an orange color with a slightly caramel aroma. Nice sweet taste with a bitter after taste. Fairly well balanced.
Pours a light orange color that doesnt scream American strong ale. Thin off white head with a piney grass aroma. Slight brown sugar taste with a nice citrusy hop flavor. Pretty good beer.
Pretty sour smelling and tasting. Not what this is but not very wit like. Dont like it much.

Pours a dark black color with a thin brown head. Heavy aromas of coffee, vanilla and chocolate. Beer is fairly dry with a burnt espresso finish. Some minor chocolate sweetness at the beginning. Pretty tasty brew.

Pours an ambery orange color with an off white head. Huge hop nose and flavors. I get pine and pine needle. Maybe some pine tar! Mmmmmmm. Bit of citrusy fruits such as a grapefruit or orange. But mostly just delicious hops. I like this one.

I have had this beer for awhile! Pours a very dark brown color with a lighter brown head. Smells of chocolate and caramel. Sort of like a chocolate bar. Taste is quite sweet! Might partly be because i have had it for so long. Little bitterness at the finish.
Smells of coriander and some grapefruit. Bit of carbonation bubbles on the tongue with a slight dry grassy feel. Some citrus and hops.
Pours a black color with a slight burnt coffee aroma. Taste is dry and butter. Slight fruityness at the very beginning that disappears quickly. Pretty good beer!
Yellow in color. Super duper white head. Tastes like a Luke warm sunrise. Hopalicious. Bam
Smells a bit like coffee which was expected. Taste is a little sweet like a fruit (plum or date) or some other nonsense like that. Aftertaste is dry and coffee like.
beer_name: Laughing Dog Anubis Imperial Coffee Porter

review_blob: Pours a super dark black color like used motor oil.  Dark brown head similar to the color of a chestnut.  Smell some coffee and whiskey!  Some chocolate in the aroma as well!  Taste is a bit chocolatey.  Has the aftertaste of whiskey.  Well rounded beer.
beer_name: Mikkeller Beer Geek Brunch Weasel (Highland Edition)

review_blob: It pours purple!  Awesome  Small to medium sized reddish purple head.  Must be the grapes, eh?  Smells of grapes and hops.  Taste is similar to what I just said.  This beer surprised me with its goodness.
